				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: New song on test<a name="72371"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 24 05 12:45 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The only thing I dont really like about the OOW runes thing is how much of a pain in the a$ it is to get the 69/70 ones.
<br />

<br />
First, they're rare as h*ll unless you're raiding. Which means if you're not a bard in a raiding guild, the chances of you getting your 69 or 70 level songs is pretty slim. Granted, there's nothing extremely special about these songs, but it would still be nice to be able to get them. 
<br />

<br />
Second, they're no drop. So unlike Kunark or Velious where there were songs that you couldn't get if you weren't in a raiding guild, you could at least save up and buy them from the more elite guilds. And as time went by, the prices came down because everyone was getting them. With the rarity of the 69/70 runes and the fact that they're no drop, it doesn't matter if everyone that's raiding gets them. You're still not going to because you're not there to loot them. On my server I keep hearing about runes rotting on raids because everyone on the raid has them all already. What's the point in that? Loot was made Attunable instead of No Drop to fix this. Why are spells/songs any different?
<br />

<br />
Lesser/Minor runes are still selling for 25k on average. Isn't that enough of a price to pay to get each of your high level songs? Apparently not since they're no drop. Never mind the fact that pretty much nobody raids GoD content on our server anymore so the chances of getting your NO DROP songs from there are pretty rare. NO DROP songs/spells suck. Period. The &quot;no duplicate&quot; method of OOW is great imo, but the runes need to be tradable or much more commonly dropped. Once DoN comes out and takes people away from OOW, runes will be even harder to come by. Declining server populations have already affected this. An expansion is going to make it worse.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
