				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: New song on test<a name="72540"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 26 05 4:15 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>You're giving normal chain pulling techniques that you need mezz for. When you don't have mezz you don't do that. Duh. It's not my normal play style. Just commenting that groups play here all the time with no CC, contrary to someone above who said you need it.
<br />

<br />
When I say cast snare till it lands, I mean start casting before 50 and don't stop. Five resists before you're in trouble. Also, if you're keeping the room clear, then not landing snare isn't such a disaster. It's only necessary there when you've just moved in or the North stairs roamers are up. 
<br />

<br />
If it is critical and if you don't have mezz, you don't leave camp till the mob is snared. So it's slower. It's safe.
