				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: New song on test<a name="72544"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 26 05 4:38 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I have all of the oow mezzes and they aren't as important as some people say they are.  In mpg, the only time youll ever get an add is if you are splitting a few nameds (6 way) or if a mob repops on the way back.  Splitting nameds can be done with snare or highsun + fade, and repops can be handled with just fade.
<br />
In rs, several camps have at most 1 add per round of clears, and that can be split the same way (and you only have to split once if you pull in the right order).
<br />
If your spells dont land, just fade.  Its no worse than a monk split, and you can probably tag a single.
<br />

<br />
Admittedly, I use mez alot in both zones, but thats because its easier, not because its necessary.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, about the new song, it would not be that great unless it stacks with the existing spell procs that several classes have.  Hopefully, it will stack for the same reason we have overhaste.  Ultimately tho, procs never seem to do as much dps as the ds songs, and 2 ds songs + overhaste + mana = 4 songs to twist mean that you have no room for that song.  Melee soloing, id take psalm over a proc any day unless i had no singing mod whatsoever, and even then its debatable.  Unless they make the proc hit very often/hard and stack with other effects, it's mainly for when you are in a group full of rogues that adds a bard at the last minute for pulling/slowing/snaring... or if you had two bards in a group.</span></td>
