				<td colspan="2"><span>Yeah, it's goofy with the other classes too. 
<br />

<br />
Like my Necro for example.. 
<br />

<br />
I have multiple runes already for spells.. One Minor, Couple Lesser, etc - BUT* our guild will likely never kill any GoD boss mobs, nor will he ever get the LDoN spells, because hardly anyone ever does LDoN anymore. So in spite of the fact that I can get some level 66-68ish spells, my chances of getting most of the GoD spells and LDoN spells are pretty much gone. 
<br />

<br />
It wouldn't be so bad if there were alternative - like the &quot;Ancient&quot; line of spells, for example. A caster could get a spell that worked fine, but he/she could also the the &quot;Ancient&quot; version of the spell, which was more mana efficient, used less components, etc. But he/she wasn't cut out of spells altogether. 
<br />

<br />
Of course, you can make due, in many cases with a substitute - but sometimes, there's just no substitute for certain spells. I really do think Sony's objective is to make spells where not everyone gets them. 
<br />

<br />
And that works, to a point - if you are in a uber guild, you'll get them all -- otherwise, sorry about your luck. 
