				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: New song on test<a name="72776"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 31 05 3:57 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>You don't need to kill GoD boss mobs to get most of your GoD spells, except the ancients. Ancients I think are meant to be rare.
<br />

<br />
The first two GoD spell runes drop in any of the first five Barindu trials. So if you have friends that also want their spells form a regular trial group and camp them. The third GoD spell is only KT and beyond, so you'll need to get through the trials for a shot at those. But they drop of single groupable mobs. Some of them are unique, ie not upgraded in OoW. The shaman slow for instance, is worth the effort to get. 
<br />

<br />
Same thing with LoDN spells. Post on your guild boards that you want to spend some time racking up the points for spells. A lot of classes have some good lodn ones. You can't just sit around moaning that no one does them anymore. Be active. Send tells out, put groups together and get it done. Even posting in /lfg and /lfp for lodns works. It takes some time, but I can always put a group together. </span></td>
